# Petralian session protocol

> Footer contract: `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\00_Brain\Conventions\Response Footer Contract.md`

Before non-trivial work on this repo, follow the vault protocol:

## Start of Session (required)
Read and execute: `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\00_Brain\_Manual Prompts\Start of Session.md`

Minimum outputs before coding:
1. Read `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\00_Brain\_Manual Prompts\Start of Session.md` and execute it
2. Read vault `_Home.md`, `Operations/AI Session Bridge.md`, `Operations/Session Summaries.md`, relevant `Features/*`
3. Read repo `memories/repo/index.md`, `open-loops.md`, `known-gotchas.md`
4. Create or update `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\40_VSCode\Petralian\Operations\Sessions\YYYY-MM-DD <topic>.md` with goal, git status, pre-scan table, roadmap (✅/⚠️/🔲)
5. Update `Operations/AI Session Bridge.md` if priority changed

## During work
- Append to today's session note after major changes
- Update Feature notes when touching a feature area

## End of Session (when user closes or asks)
Read: `D:\Obsidian\Obsidian\00_Brain\_Manual Prompts\End of Session.md`

Minimum outputs:
1. Append one entry to `Operations/Session Summaries.md`
2. Update `Operations/Open Loops.md`; update `Operations/Copilot Shared Memory.md` only if that note exists
3. Sync `memories/repo/open-loops.md` with vault open loops
4. Session footer per Response Footer Contract (self-improvements, next priority, deploy status)
5. Update `.claude/NOTES.md` and Feature notes with durable lessons

Do not skip Obsidian updates because the user asked for code only — protocol and code ship together.
